Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Systems Engineer I* position with *Aflac*. I bring over three years of professional experience in distributed systems, cloud infrastructure, and multi-platform operations, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade distributed systems that directly reflect the technical depth and operational rigor this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected and maintained a distributed multi-platform system handling 1,000+ platform endpoints with safe, validated tool calls — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and internal controls across microservices to ensure system compliance. To keep these systems production-ready, I built comprehensive observability and monitoring infrastructure using Langfuse and LangSmith with structured logs and tracing to track system performance, debug distributed application issues, and maintain service levels, reducing latency by 60%. I also designed disaster recovery workflows and change management processes for concurrent multi-agent orchestration, enabling reliable coordination and problem solving across complex distributed workflows — directly mirroring the disaster recovery planning, change management, and system performance optimization responsibilities central to this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic distributed infrastructure Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across Google Cloud Storage, AWS S3, and MinIO through expiring signed URLs, supporting multi-platform environment operations. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications at enterprise level, implementing security protocols and access controls — giving me direct experience with the kind of enterprise-scale infrastructure support, system compliance, and security standards implementation this role requires. Additionally, I developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent AWS Lambda timeouts, ensuring system performance optimization and capacity management. Together, these roles have prepared me to provide support on design and maintenance of multi-platform environments for distributed on-premise and cloud infrastructure, troubleshoot and analyze complex issues specific to a broad range of infrastructure products, and contribute meaningfully to Aflac's core systems engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in distributed processing, system operations, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Aflac values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for distributed processing of model training and fine-tuning workloads. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from data preparation and training runs to implementing secure model serving infrastructure using vLLM for inference with Hugging Face deployment, ensuring data integrity and system compliance with security standards. Beyond building the systems myself, I led technical workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the knowledge-sharing and proactive training responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Aflac's Digital Services team.

I have always been passionate about providing the best value for consumers and putting people first, and envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Aflac's mission of providing financial protection and exceptional service to policyholders. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

